e_level)]\n  }\n  \n  # ORDER AND CHECK MONOTONICITY\n  order <- order(quantile_level)\n  predicted <- predicted[order]\n  if (!all(diff(predicted) >= 0)) {\n    cli_abort(c(\"!\" = \"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level.\"))\n  }\n  \n  # Continue with bias calculation...\n  median_prediction <- interpolate_median(predicted, quantile_level)\n  # ... rest of bias calculation logic\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `assert_forecast.forecast_quantile` - FULL METHOD\n\n**Location:** `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/class-forecast-quantile.R`, lines 81-89\n\n**Exact Code:**\n```r\n#' @export\n#' @rdname assert_forecast\n#' @keywords validate-forecast-object\nassert_forecast.forecast_quantile <- function(\n  forecast, forecast_type = NULL, verbose = TRUE, ...\n) {\n  assert(check_columns_present(forecast, \"quantile_level\"))\n  forecast <- assert_forecast_generic(forecast, verbose)\n  assert_forecast_type(forecast, actual = \"quantile\", desired = forecast_type)\n  assert_numeric(forecast$quantile_level, lower = 0, upper = 1)\n  return(invisible(NULL))\n}\n```\n\n**What It Currently Checks:**\n1. ✅ Presence of `quantile_level` column\n2. ✅ Generic checks via `assert_forecast_generic()` (duplicates, NA count info, column names)\n3. ✅ Forecast type matches expected type\n4. ✅ `quantile_level` values are numeric and in [0, 1] range\n\n**What It Does NOT Check:**\n- ❌ Monotonicity: predictions don't decrease with increasing quantile level\n- ❌ No early warning before scoring\n- ❌ No user-facing diagnostic function\n\n**Connection to Generic Checks (`assert_forecast_generic`):**\nThe generic validation (lines 112-159 of `R/class-forecast.R`) checks:\n- Data is a data.table with min 1 row\n- Columns `observed` and `predicted` present\n- Either `quantile_level` OR `sample_id` present (but not both)\n- No duplicate forecasts\n- NA row handling with vague message: \"Some rows containing NA values may be removed. This is fine if not unexpected.\" (lines 148-152)\n\n---\n\n### 3. TEST PATTERNS - QUANTILE FORECAST TESTS\n\n#### `test-class-forecast-quantile.R` Structure:\n\n**Core Tests (lines 5-67):**\n- Basic conversion: `as_forecast_quantile()` works with various input formats\n- Error handling: missing columns, wrong types, duplicates\n- Rounding issues: handles floating-point rounding in quantile_level\n- Data.frame vs data.table compatibility\n- Conversion from sample forecasts: `as_forecast_quantile.forecast_sample()`\n\n**Example Pattern (lines 56-67):**\n```r\ntest_that(\"as_forecast_quantile() function throws an error with duplicate forecasts\", {\n  example <- rbind(\n    example_quantile,\n    example_quantile[1000:1010]\n  )\n\n  expect_error(\n    suppressMessages(suppressWarnings(as_forecast_quantile(example))),\n    \"Assertion on 'data' failed: There are instances with more than one forecast for the same target...\", \n    fixed = TRUE\n  )\n})\n```\n\n#### `test-metrics-quantile.R` - Bias Tests (lines 709-903):\n\n**Test Patterns:**\n```r\n# Lines 837-850: Quantile ordering constraint\ntest_that(\"bias_quantile(): quantiles must be increasing\", {\n  predicted <- 1:4\n  quantiles <- c(0.8, 0.3, 0.5, 0.9)  # BAD: not ordered\n  \n  expect_error(\n    bias_quantile(observed = 3, predicted, quantiles),\n    \"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level\"\n  )\n})\n\n# Lines 852-861: Prediction monotonicity constraint\ntest_that(\"bias_quantile(): predictions must be increasing\", {\n  predicted <- c(1, 2, 4, 3)  # BAD: not monotonic\n  quantiles <- c(0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.9)\n  \n  expect_error(\n    bias_quantile(observed = 3, predicted, quantiles),\n    \"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level\"\n  )\n})\n\n# Lines 863-876: Quantile level uniqueness\ntest_that(\"bias_quantile(): quantile levels must be unique\", {\n  predicted <- 1:4\n  quantiles <- c(0.3, 0.3, 0.5, 0.8)  # BAD: duplicates\n  \n  expect_error(\n    bias_quantile(observed = 3, predicted, quantiles),\n    \"Assertion on 'quantile_level' failed: Contains duplicated values, position 2.\"\n  )\n})\n```\n\n**Key Test Conventions:**\n- Use both `expect_error()` and `expect_silent()` for passing cases\n- Suppress messages/warnings in conversion calls: `suppressMessages(suppressWarnings(...))`\n- Test both edge cases (NA handling, matrix input) and error conditions\n- Use `expect_no_condition()` for validation that should pass without output\n\n---\n\n### 4. HELPER PATTERN - `get_duplicate_forecasts()`\n\n**Location:** `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/get-duplicate-forecasts.R`, lines 19-48\n\n**Full Function:**\n```r\nget_duplicate_forecasts <- function(\n  data,\n  forecast_unit = NULL,\n  counts = FALSE\n) {\n  assert_data_frame(data)\n  data <- ensure_data.table(data)\n\n  if (!is.null(forecast_unit)) {\n    data <- set_forecast_unit(data, forecast_unit)\n  }\n  forecast_unit <- get_forecast_unit(data)\n  available_type <- c(\"sample_id\", \"quantile_level\", \"predicted_label\") %in% colnames(data)\n  type <- c(\"sample_id\", \"quantile_level\", \"predicted_label\")[available_type]\n  data <- as.data.table(data)\n  data[, scoringutils_InternalDuplicateCheck := .N, by = c(forecast_unit, type)]\n  out <- data[scoringutils_InternalDuplicateCheck > 1]\n\n  col <- colnames(data)[\n    colnames(data) %in% c(\"sample_id\", \"quantile_level\", \"predicted_label\")\n  ]\n  setorderv(out, cols = c(forecast_unit, col, \"predicted\"))\n  out[, scoringutils_InternalDuplicateCheck := NULL]\n\n  if (counts) {\n    out <- out[, .(n_duplicates = .N), by = c(get_forecast_unit(out))]\n  }\n\n  return(out[])\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern for `get_non_monotonic_forecasts()` to follow:**\n1. Accept `data` (forecast object)\n2. Accept optional `forecast_unit` parameter\n3. Accept optional `counts` parameter (for aggregated output)\n4. Use `get_forecast_unit()` to identify grouping columns\n5. Identify type-specific column (`quantile_level` for quantiles)\