ck happens in `bias_quantile_single_vector()` (internal function, lines 474-527)\n- It's a **hard error** using `cli_abort()`, not a warning\n- Occurs AFTER reordering predictions by quantile level to ensure proper alignment\n- Happens AFTER handling NA values (lines 480-491)\n- The check uses `diff(predicted) >= 0` to verify monotonic non-decreasing predictions\n\n**Full `bias_quantile_single_vector` Function Structure:**\n```r\nbias_quantile_single_vector <- function(observed, predicted,\n                                        quantile_level, na.rm) {\n  assert_number(observed)\n  \n  # Handle NAs\n  predicted_has_NAs <- anyNA(predicted)\n  quantile_has_NAs <- anyNA(quantile_level)\n  \n  if (any(predicted_has_NAs, quantile_has_NAs)) {\n    if (!na.rm) {\n      return(NA_real_)\n    }\n    quantile_level <- quantile_level[!is.na(predicted)]\n    predicted <- predicted[!is.na(predicted)]\n    predicted <- predicted[!is.na(quantile_level)]\n    quantile_level <- quantile_level[!is.na(quantile_level)]\n  }\n  \n  # ORDER AND CHECK MONOTONICITY\n  order <- order(quantile_level)\n  predicted <- predicted[order]\n  if (!all(diff(predicted) >= 0)) {\n    cli_abort(c(\"!\" = \"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level.\"))\n  }\n  \n  # Continue with bias calculation...\n  median_prediction <- interpolate_median(predicted, quantile_level)\n  # ... rest of bias calculation logic\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `assert_forecast.forecast_quantile` - FULL METHOD\n\n**Location:** `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/class-forecast-quantile.R`, lines 81-89\n\n**Exact Code:**\n```r\n#' @export\n#' @rdname assert_forecast\n#' @keywords validate-forecast-object\nassert_forecast.forecast_quantile <- function(\n  forecast, forecast_type = NULL, verbose = TRUE, ...\n) {\n  assert(check_columns_present(forecast, \"quantile_level\"))\n  forecast <- assert_forecast_generic(forecast, verbose)\n  assert_forecast_type(forecast, actual = \"quantile\", desire