es 709-903):\n\n**Test Patterns:**\n```r\n# Lines 837-850: Quantile ordering constraint\ntest_that(\"bias_quantile(): quantiles must be increasing\", {\n  predicted <- 1:4\n  quantiles <- c(0.8, 0.3, 0.5, 0.9)  # BAD: not ordered\n  \n  expect_error(\n    bias_quantile(observed = 3, predicted, quantiles),\n    \"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level\"\n  )\n})\n\n# Lines 852-861: Prediction monotonicity constraint\ntest_that(\"bias_quantile(): predictions must be increasing\", {\n  predicted <- c(1, 2, 4, 3)  # BAD: not monotonic\n  quantiles <- c(0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.9)\n  \n  expect_error(\n    bias_quantile(observed = 3, predicted, quantiles),\n    \"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level\"\n  )\n})\n\n# Lines 863-876: Quantile level uniqueness\ntest_that(\"bias_quantile(): quantile levels must be unique\", {\n  predicted <- 1:4\n  quantiles <- c(0.3, 0.3, 0.5, 0.8)  # BAD: duplicates\n  \n  expect_error(\n    bias_quantile(observed = 3, predicted, quantiles),\n    \"Assertion on 'quantile_level' failed: Contains duplicated values, position 2.\"\n  )\n})\n```\n\n**Key Test Conventions:**\n- Use both `expect_error()` and `expect_silent()` for passing cases\n- Suppress messages/warnings in conversion calls: `suppressMessages(suppressWarnings(...))`\n- Test both edge cases (NA handling, matrix input) and error conditions\n- Use `expect_no_condition()` for validation that should pass without output\n\n---\n\n### 4. HELPER PATTERN - `get_duplicate_forecasts()`\n\n**Location:** `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/get-duplicate-forecasts.R`, lines 19-48\n\n**Full Function:**\n```r\nget_duplicate_forecasts <- function(\n  data,\n  forecast_unit = NULL,\n  counts = FALSE\n) {\n  assert_data_frame(data)\n  data <- ensure_data.table(data)\n\n  if (!is.null(forecast_unit)) {\n    data <- set_forecast_unit(data, forecast_unit)\n  }\n  forecast_unit <- get_forecast_unit(data)\n  available_type <- c(\"sample_id\